FBIS4-1499 "drafr083_cs94023" FBIS-AFR-94-083-S Daily Report 29 Apr 1994 REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA Violent Incidents Reported at Polling Stations Violent Incidents Reported at Polling Stations Suspected Right-Wingers Arrested MB2904123094 Johannesburg SAPA in English 1202 GMT 29 Apr 94 MB2904123094 Johannesburg SAPA English BFN [Report by K. Swart] [Text] Pretoria April 29 SAPA -- Seven men with possible rightwing links have been arrested at Betanie in the Odi Region, police in Bophuthatswana said on Friday [29 April]. A police spokesman said the men had allegedly attempted to intimidate Betanie residents into not voting, SABC [South African Broadcasting Corporation] radio news reported.
